headline.main: PRINCE PAUL TALKS WITH REICH ENVOY; Said to Have Pledged Belgrade to 'Favorable' Consideration of Pact in Near Future PRINCE PAUL TALKS WITH REICH ENVOY

lead_paragraph: ZAGREB, Yugoslavia, March 2 -- The probability that Yugoslavia soon would sign the Axis three-power pact was reported in authoritative quarters tonight. These sources said that this probability had resulted from conferences between Prince Paul, the Yugoslav Regent, and Viktor yon Heeren, German Minister to Belgrade.
